text: Wonderful Alexander and the Catwings is the third book in a series of four American children's picture books written by Ursula K. Le Guin. S. D. Schindler made the pictures. Scholastic published the book in 1994. It tells the stories of kittens who were born with wings. Category:American children's books Category:Books by Ursula K. Le Guin Category:1994 books
title: Wonderful Alexander and the Catwings
